column5: Sounds  like a ducky of a day you had Sinker.  Once the cold comes were going to hook up for some wing ding,n.

Don't wait until it gets too cold Misfish. Its starting to get good now. We shot all new birds today, so they're coming. Anytime now and we'll be in full migration.  Just shoot me a date and I'll see if I can work it in.  Sinker
By the sounds of those winds it was a good day to be at work.  Time to go home now.  Good to see that everyone seemed to enjoy the day.  I'll enjoy the overtime on the next pay cheque!
getting geared & ready for 5 days of Muskie fishing here; food, booze all the typicals
House work.. Yard work.. House work and Computer work.... and the winds a howling outside... but I'll be ready for the water's NEXT weekend...lol
Pikeie and I did get out this am for some river fishing . One break off was all we had.  Was supposed to be on Quinte but have rescheduled for next Sunday.  TB

Well ... my neighbor and I went out to a local reservoir up in the mountains this morning.  Just had a front move through yesterday and overnight.  The reservoir allows electric motors only.   With winds, white caps, and only a trolling motor to use ... we gave up after a few hours.  Not hits, not bites, no nothin ..... just getting blown around.  Had a good time chatting and passing the time.  Gonna give it another go here before long.
Just curious, I'm at work or I'd be fishing.    Weather looks great here in the big smoke, warm and overcast the when I came in this morning.  So what's your excuse.     Now back too work for me.
Working today,but going to be putting the smack down on them Simcoe smallies Sunday with my pal Terry.
My wife has gone for a girls weekend to some spa. I've got three kids here and two of them aren't mine. This gives me leverage for the next while, though.
I'm at work procrastinating.  Wishing I was fishing.  So this will have to do!!!
My wife has a girls night tonight!!! Thus allowing me to commence the hunt for walleye at 4:30pm

Going to Hamilton in about a hour to look at a boat to buy!! Meeting Gerritt there at 1:30 this afternoon...with a bit of luck, we'll be boat owners and no longer shore locked.  Going to Rice Lake tomorrow with my cousin to chase down some muskies or smallies.  Sucks you are working Will....hopefully you get out tomorrow as planned.  If I buy this boat today, then I'll cancel the appointment for tomorrow....so you can fish longer....LOL.

There is other thing I like to do at this time of year (apart from fishing). It is almost like fishing but muuuuuuch cheaper  . Yesterday I was in the woods and picked up couple of decent size baskets of the wild mushrooms ( before you start: they are not magic   ), so today I'm making them ready for consumption (drying and pickling) and trying new recipes.  Delicious
busy stringing new line on my reels for fishing sunday...

Good luck on the boat ccmtcanada.  I know when I got mine I couldn't wait to get off the shore line.  Unfortunately nothing was open so all I could do is zoom around looking for spots.  You've got lots of time to get in some prime fishing!
Thanks cranks!  Hopefully it pans out for us...we are pretty excited.  One way or another though, we will be on the water by spring.
well i am stuck at work today, and when i get outta here if the winds are to bad i will molesting eyes and skis on sturgeon lake
If I could I would
if it wasent downpouring and gusting 50 kms hr id think about dropping the boat in,the weather has been crap for a solid week now
Lunch today with girlfriends Grandmother Tomorrow the Bass had better fear me. If I eat her cooking... tomorrow everyone will fear my  Hookset.
I'm working too ......... or at least I'm at work LOL.
Dont forget the hooks,they will come in handy.  I dont find the wind that bad up here. Guess a south west is better then a north east.
Well, it seems the gods have smiled on me and I was able to free myself of children for the day!!! Now I just have to figure out if it's going to be trout or 'skis....Either way

Been overdosing on cold medicine for 3 days now so that I'll be able to head out on the water tomorrow - one more day of rest and I'll be good to go (and if I'm still sick I'm still going - been two weeks without fishing!)
Dont you just hate this time of year. either hunting or great fishing to be had,and that darn cold thing starts. Sucks big time.  Get well soon TB.

I got pretty close....drive over to Orillia and blew $320 in Tromblys Tacklebox !  New 7'6 Heavy Shimano Compre to put my CT-700B on for trolling, some #0 and #1 snap swivels and swivels for BOQ, some Fin-S minnows for ice fishin........  And if POURED rain on the way home and the lakes are ROUGH.
If you seen the swells on sturgeon lake rate now you would understand why I'm not out. Hopefully get out later today or tommorrow. Cheers Jeff
They must be bad if they're keeping you on shore Jeff! -Brian
wind gust to 40k right now and same for tomorrow in bradford

I left for work when it was still dark, i could hear the swells smashing off my boathouse, so yea sturgeon lake was a little rough, or i guess i can take the tin missle over to emily and explore through threre

I was out duck hunting this morning, got our limits, so now I"m just hangin out.......havin a few cold ones  If the wind dies down a bit tomorrow, I might go for a bucket of  perch.......not looking good, but I'm off all week  Sinker
